The paper deals with the problem of publishing personal data while preserving privacy, which is a common concern in the field of database systems (cs.DB) and cryptography (cs.CR). The k-anonymity approach is a clustering-based technique, which involves grouping similar records together, and is related to the field of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the k-anonymity problem, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
